mpimemu
------------------------------------------
This distribution contains the source code for mpimemu, a simple tool that
helps approximate MPI library memory usage as a function of scale.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.2.0-1
  libopenmpi40-4.1.0-1
  perl_base-5.32.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.36.1-2
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-10.2.0-1
  libopenmpi-devel-4.1.0-1
  make-4.3-1
  openmpi-4.1.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://hpc.github.io/mpimemu/

Canonical download:
  https://hpc.github.io/mpimemu/dists/mpimemu-1.3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack mpimemu-1.3-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./mpimemu-1.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/mpimemu-1.3-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/mpimemu-1.3-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(mpimemu)
  /usr/bin/mpimemu-mkstats
  /usr/bin/mpimemu-plot
  /usr/bin/mpimemu-run
  /usr/bin/mpimemu.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/mpimemu.README
  /usr/share/doc/mpimemu/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/mpimemu/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/mpimemu/Copyright
  /usr/share/doc/mpimemu/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/mpimemu/README
  /usr/share/doc/mpimemu/README.QUICKSTART
  /usr/share/doc/mpimemu/THANKS
  /usr/share/doc/mpimemu/TODO

